summary: So, my mum likes Good Omens too. She really didn’t intend to. In fact right up to the end of the first episode she really didn’t...
body:
So, my mum likes Good Omens too. She really didn’t intend to. In fact right up to the end of the first episode she really didn’t like it. I lit she realised that Terry Pratchett co-wrote the book, and all of a sudden she was watching the episodes just as quickly as I was.

She was less enthused when she found out that I was re-reading the book and writing fic. “Oh no. An obsession!” she said. And honestly, she’s now wrong. It’s like a switch is flipped in my brain and I go from “I like this” to “this is my entire reason for being” and she can tell. Every time. And she hates it.

But then she asked about the fic. And now she wants to read the fic, and I’m not sure how to deal with that, because I’ve been writing fic for over 20 years and she has never once expressed any interest in reading it. I can’t give her a link because it would allow her to find my entire online persona and I can’t handle that.

On the plus side, my mum is finally taking an interest in my interests. So that’s good, I guess…

summary: I’m currently reading Neil Gaiman’s Good Omens script book and I am thoroughly enjoying it, especially these directions and...
body:
I’m currently reading Neil Gaiman’s Good Omens script book and I am thoroughly enjoying it, especially these directions and little notes sprinkled about. Here are my favorites:

The nanny, wearing dark glasses, reminds us of Crowley. She’s sexy and domineering.

The plants are terrified. No, I don’t know how we show this on television either.

Crowley flares at him, glarefully.

HUGE EXPLOSION. FIRE AND LIGHT AND THINGS BEING BLOWN AROUND. SO COOL AN EXPLOSION THAT I AM TYPING IN CAPITALS.

Crowley’s bedroom. We see a montage of Crowley trying to get to sleep by lying on the bed, on the wall, then on the ceiling. CLOSE UP of his snake-eyes. He’s wide-awake. Then he puts on his dark glasses.

Can someone please draw Crowley attempting to fall asleep in all of those places and then calling Aziraphale to meet up at their third (romantic) rendezvous!!!
